# Image Optimisation

## Encoder
- ALWAYS use **sharp** for raster → WebP conversion. No other encoders.
- Production WebP settings: **quality 78**, **effort 6** (matches `src/media_namer/constants.js`).

## Byte gate (mandatory)
- NEVER replace an existing WebP in place unless the candidate file is **≥5% smaller** than the original (`new_bytes <= original_bytes * 0.95`).
- ALWAYS write candidates to a scratch/temp path first; swap only after the byte gate passes.
- ALWAYS record every attempt in `scratchpad/optimise-report.csv` before any in-place replacement.

## In-place WebP re-encode
- NEVER re-encode a live WebP in place without a prior `scratchpad/optimise-report.csv` row for that file.
- NEVER bulk re-encode without a dry-run or report pass.

## process_all_images.js
- NEVER run `src/media_namer/process_all_images.js` without an explicit **`--dry-run`** (or equivalent preview) first.
- Full flatten/rename pipelines are separate from live WebP optimisation — do not conflate them.

## Staging orphans
- Manifest-only / unused assets go to `src/public_html/images/_staging/hinterland-unused/`.
- NEVER permanently delete staged originals until the site owner confirms.
- After staging moves, prune only the corresponding entries from `path-manifest.json`.

## Canonical tree
- `src/public_html/` is canonical for HTML references and deployed images.
- Source rasters live under project-root `images/`; outputs under `src/public_html/images/`.

## Lists
- `scratchpad/live-images.json` — HTML-referenced WebPs (optimise targets).
- `scratchpad/staging-images.json` — manifest-only orphans (staging targets).
